      "proposed_override_text": "Lodge's cooking surface is bare cast iron — no nonstick coating, no PFAS, no plastic-based layer between food and pan. Cast iron is an inert metal that doesn't transfer plastic-associated chemicals into food, even under high-heat cooking, which is why it earns one of the highest PAC Safety Scores in cookware. Seasoned cast iron also develops a natural, durable cooking surface over time.",
